OpenSSL additional feature

Support ChaCha20+Poly1305 cipher suites.
For Debian/Ubuntu packages.

How to make packages:

*Debian 7 (wheezy)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openssl
  tar xf openssl_1.0.1e.orig.tar.gz
  cd openssl-1.0.1e
  tar xvf ../openssl_1.0.1e-2+deb7u18.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/wheezy/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

*Debian 8 (jessie)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openssl
  tar xf openssl_1.0.1k.orig.tar.gz
  cd openssl-1.0.1k
  tar xvf ../openssl_1.0.1k-3+deb8u2.debian.tar.xz
  cp -a (this repository)/jessie/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

*Ubuntu 12.04 LTS (precise)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openssl
  tar xf openssl_1.0.1.orig.tar.gz
  cd openssl-1.0.1
  tar xvf ../openssl_1.0.1-4ubuntu5.31.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/precise/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

*Ubuntu 14.04 LTS (trusty)
  (in some directory)
  apt-get -d source openssl
  tar xf openssl_1.0.1f.orig.tar.gz
  cd openssl-1.0.1f
  tar xvf ../openssl_1.0.1f-1ubuntu2.15.debian.tar.gz
  cp -a (this repository)/trusty/debian/* debian/
  debuild -uc -us

